1. Run architector to document/check each of the four layers in a separate doc each
2. The `Analysis` singleton creates a hidden global dependency that couples rendering directly to analysis logic and complicates testing.
3. Scene re-upload on every dirty frame re-generates *all* geometry CPU-side and re-uploads to the GPU, which will not scale beyond small models.
4. The slicing infrastructure (used by 4 of 5 analyses) recomputes the full Z-bounds scan for every analysis independently, resulting in redundant O(V) passes.
5. Learn more about O(V) and o(V)
6. Understand pathway to testing - what tests to use, how to create, if anything needs refactoring for testability
7. Analysis invocation alternatives - reccommended change
8. Review "The vendored GLFW headers are unused dead weight." - Headers included in Camera.hpp but SDL3 is the actual backend. Should be removed.
9. Each analysis independently scans Z-bounds and calls Slice::Range()	Pre-compute slices once per solid, share across analyses
10. CMakeLists.txt duplicates the source list (once in set(SOURCES ...), again in add_executable). The SOURCES variable is never referenced — only the inline list is used.
11. camera.cpp is listed twice in the source list.
12. Include path ${DMAKE_SOURCE_DIR} (typo for ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}) for earcut is silently broken.
13. Consider Analysis running async, only triggereing from render loop, but not blocking it
14. Consider some sort of shading in the future
15. !!! Review and fix non-confotming best practices

